About Rockland Luggage Since its inception in 1998, Rockland by Fox Luggage has been proudly producing quality luggage and bags for the style savvy traveler. Recognized for its graphic and colorful designs, Rockland prides itself on creating products influenced by current trends in design and fashion. Our products turn heads in a crowd and stand out in the baggage carousel, making it easy for quick exits out the airport. Affordable and travel resistant, Rockland bags are an ideal companion for everything from quick trips to the gym to overnight getaways to extended vacations. Our selection includes: luggage sets (4 piece, 3 piece or 2 piece), hard cases, soft cases, carry ons, rolling backpacks, travel duffels, rolling duffels, cosmetic bags, and kids' backpacks. Over the years, a few Rockland products have been featured in film and television. Their colorful designs make them ideal for an eye catching visual element on screen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great little carry on luggage!
reviews.reviewText: My son used this to go on a 2 weeks trip. Fit everything he needed and still weighed less than 30 lbs. The bag is lightweight and sturdy enough. It tends to want to fall over one side if not placed on a very smooth flat surface. Not a bad deal at all for the price and its quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2016
reviews.reviewText: It was a few days before March 13th and I really needed a new luggage for my trip to Japan. My previous two roller carry on lost a wheel and was a pain to bring along because it had no spinners. I found this decently priced luggage around Amazon and I decided to test my luck and see if this would hold up for the trip. It was also available for prime shipping and I got this relatively fast so I was able to pack all my clothes in a timely manner.I traveled to Japan for two weeks and the luggage was definitely a good choice. It fitted 3 pairs of jeans, 10 shirts, 10 undershirts, 10 boxers, 15 pairs of socks, 2 sweat pants, and a small bag of cosmetics. The handle and wheels seemed flimsy but it survived the entire trip no problem. As long as the roads were smooth there was no problem traveling with the luggage but it does get tough to pull when the road is bumpy which resorted me to having to to tilt the luggage and carry on it's two wheel.There was also no problem at customs or bag checks as the bag was the correct size for all domestic and international flights to bring on board the plane. I definitely will be using this again for more future trips.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Lightweight, but unstable
reviews.reviewText: Ok so I've used this suitcase for multiple trips and flights since 2016 and the seams and zippers have held up well. The lightweight nature of the suitcase is nice when you are carrying it, but it falls over often and it isn't very stable. Fits well in overhead bins and the orange color stands out well when I'm looking for it on the baggage carousel though!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Only buy this if you are in a real time crunch
reviews.reviewText: I bought this product because the price was good and the shipping was fast. I bought 2 of them but only took one on my trip. Within the first 10 minutes the pull out handle broke and would not go back in. I had to turn it upside down and slam it on the ground everytime I needed to stow it. Safe to say I'm sending the other one back. It is lightweight and not bad looking, and at least covered the immediate need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got this bag for short trips. It is lightweight and is the correct size for most airlines. Hate checking bags so it works great.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok for a budget bag
reviews.reviewText: The size of this suitcase is good, no issues getting it into the overhead bin. I’ve taken it on three trips so far and it has held up well so it seems pretty well made. I like the various pockets, they are well placed and of sufficient size to give me ready access to all the things I need to get to when traveling. What I’m not as thrilled with is that this suitcase has a strong tendency to tip over because the wheels are so close together. I’ve also had issues with the wheels not being able to freely rotate, making it difficult to pull. I often feel like I’m just dragging the suitcase along the floor and there aren’t wheels at all.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great size for international flights
reviews.reviewText: The suitcase is the perfect size for travel where you can't carry too much weight. It fits in the overhead well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on December 4, 2018
reviews.reviewText: Bought this for a short trip to Venice. Perfect size for the cabin on Easyjet. It withstood pouring rain and being dragged around the bridges and cobbles of Venice by teenage daughter with no trouble. The swivel wheels were very useful. Great item and great price. We look forward to using it again.

Am at the airport having struggled to get this awful case to wheel properly. The handle doesn’t lock low enough to control it if wheeling upright. The wheels don’t work well on carpeted areas and take the case where you don’t want it at other times. It tips forward if the contents aren’t arranged with all weight at the bottom and to the back. Not worth getting if it’s to be used as cabin baggage. Will get another brand before flying back.
